Generic service oriented IPC libary framework for generating skeleton and stub code 
from a high-level interface description directly in C++ by the C++ compiler.


Features
========

Interface level

 * shoot-and-forget requests
 * requests with associated responses or error responses
 * signals 
 * event driven interface
 * blocking (RPC) call interface


Transport level

 * currently only sequential packet UNIX domain sockets (local transport only) 


Possible future features

 * TCP transport
 * UDP/datagram transport for signals and shoot-and-forget requests
 * Attributes with appropriate notifications (value changes...)
 * multithread support 
   * send requests from other threads
   * receive events in thread-pool